On Flushing Avenue in the Bushwick neighborhood of Brooklyn, lies a Puerto Rican restaurant called Norwinds.  Google Maps says it’s a funky Puerto Rican cafe. I guess it could be considered funky, maybe it’s the neighborhood. I decided on the Hiberito sandwich even before I arrived based on a google picture. Instead of bread, they use two broad pieces of fried plantain and put strips of steak with lettuce, tomato and their special sauce in between.  Unique and delicious. In the Age of Covid, we ate outside in the new normal of street dining.   Melissa was our gracious server who was friendly, patient and efficient. We now have a new go-to spot in Bushwick.
Under the "new norm" rules overall, it was pleasant, the food/drinks were Great. The Manager on staff tonight, Yvonne, was truly on point in her service and customersatisfaction.

This past Sunday I was a guest at a gender reveal party here and enjoyed the time spent. The place is typical of a bar on the inside but the outdoor area is quite large and goes very deep to the back. It is probably a great place to be on a Friday or Saturday evening with a bunch of friends. The beers were cold and the food had plenty of flavor. The staff was great and they came around to our table on a regular basis to make sure that we had everything we needed to make the afternoon go by as smoothly as possible. The DJ playing outside was spinning a lot of the old classic R&B hits which resonated well with the older crowd in attendance. Overall, really good place.
